    <p>
        <b>1.Trekking</b></p>
    <p>
     &nbsp;<img alt="" class="style7" src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/auli3.jpg" /></p>
     <p>The majestic snow-capped mountains of Kuari Pass have been the prime attraction of trekkers worldwide for several years. The alpine meadows are the perfect destination for backpackers who enjoy hiking with friends. As it is at an altitude of 12,000 ft, that’s why this place can offer unparalleled stunning views.

</p>
<p>Apart from endless blankets of snowy land, you can also explore the grand green forests. On this trek, trekkers can enjoy the breathtaking view of the Mt. Nanda Devi summit. Most interestingly, during your trekking, you can also get a chance to have meaningful interaction with the local tribes.</p>

 
       <p><b>2. Enjoy India’s highest ropeway ride</b></p> 
       
   <img alt="" class="style8" src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/auli2.jpg" />

            <p>If you are planning to visit this unique place, then make sure to explore the exciting cable car ride. This outstanding ropeway connects Joshimath to Auli. As per the information, this sprawling ropeway comes under one of India’s longest and highest ropeways.

</p>
<p>By riding this ropeway, you can reach unbelievable heights within no time. You will get a fantastic experience once the ride gets over. From this cable car ride, you can explore the views of the lush green forests and snow-laden valleys.</p>

   
    <p><b>3.Explore Skiing</b></p>
<p>
    <img alt="" class="style9" src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/auli1.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
    &nbsp;<p>If you want to explore the best skiing activities in India, then Auli is the best place to visit. In December, this place is snowcapped and covered with evergreen conifers; that’s why during the winter season, this place creates a perfect place for Skiing.

</p>
<p>Most interestingly, not just in India, Mt Nanda Devi Kamet Skiing is also considered the best skiing destination worldwide. While enjoying Skiing, tourists can see several stunning views of Dunagiri mountain peaks..</p>
